item.title: Stagnation Worries Weigh on Euro

item.description: SAS swung to a bigger-than-expected net profit in the third quarter as higher demand drove a 54% rise in revenue.

item.title: Salzgitter Withdraws Outlook After Aurubis Problems
item.description: Salzgitter suspended its earnings guidance for 2023 after its Aurubis unit said thieves had stolen copper with a value in the three-digit-million-euro range, prompting a profit warning.

item.title: Eurozone Bond Yields Edge Up But Signs of Economic Weakness Gain Traction
item.description: Eurozone government bond yields edged higher but remained off recent highs amid mounting evidence the economy is weakening, Commerzbank Research said.
